      • getProgId

        public List<ProgId> getProgId()
        The version-independent ProgId must be the first child element of actual ProgId. Nesting other ProgId elements within the Version-independent ProgId will create COM+ aliases, see 
         <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><html:a xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/wix/2006/wi" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xse="http://schemas.microsoft.com/wix/2005/XmlSchemaExtension" href="http://support.microsoft.com/kb/305745">http://support.microsoft.com/kb/305745</html:a>
        for more information.Gets the value of the progId property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the progId property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getProgId().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list ProgId

      • getExtension

        public List<Extension> getExtension()
        Extensions that refer to this ProgId Gets the value of the extension property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the extension property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getExtension().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Extension
